ns), `AGENT_KEY` (registry key), and `AGENT_SLUG` (kebab-case for filesystem) — important distinctions that were previously conflated.\\n\\n- **Scope clarification.** Explicitly scoping to hook-capable agents (implementing `HookSupport`) and pointing to `agent.go` for interface definitions.\\n\\n- **Commit checkpoints between phases.** Each phase/step now ends with a `/commit` reminder, which prevents losing work during long multi-phase runs.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Issues\\n\\n**Typo:**\\n- `implement.md` line 8: `\\\"E2E-first Test driven develpoment\\\"` — \\\"develpoment\\\" should be \\\"development\\\"\\n\\n**Researcher is now too restricted:**\\n- `researcher.md` adds `\\\"**Do NOT read other internal Entire source files** beyond agent-guide.md\\\"`. This seems overly restrictive. The researcher's job is to understand compatibility, and skimming `event.go` (to see actual EventType constants) or `agent.go` (to see the interface) would help produce a more accurate hook-to-EventType mapping table. The agent-guide.md may not always be perfectly in sync with the source. Consider softening to \\\"prefer agent-guide.md, but may reference event.go/agent.go for exact names.\\\"\\n\\n**Step 6 in implementer.md has inconsistent lint-only instruction:**\\n- The \\\"Core Principle\\\" section says `\\\"No unit tests during Steps 4-13\\\"` and `\\\"Format and lint, don't unit test\\\"`, but Step 3 says `\\\"mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test\\\"`. The distinction is explained as \\\"compile-only sanity check\\\" but `mise run test` runs actual tests, not just compilation. If you truly want compile-only, use `go build ./...` instead. This could confuse agents into running the full test suite between every E2E tier.\\n\\n**E2E flakiness guidance could be stronger:**\\n- Step 13 acknowledges flakiness (`\\\"E2E tests can be flaky when run all at once\\\"`) but the mitigation is just \\\"re-run individually.\\\" Consider documenting known flakiness patterns or whether there's a sequential-only flag.\\n\\n**Missing rollback guidance:**\\n- The old doc had guidance on what to do if a step produces bad code. The new doc focuses on the happy path (run, fail, fix, repeat) but doesn't address what happens if an implementation for Tier N breaks a previously-passing Tier M. Adding a note like \\\"if a passing tier regresses, fix the regression before advancing\\\" would help.\\n\\n**Test-writer phase lost useful content:**\\n- The old `test-writer.md` had a full example of how to write agent-specific test scenarios (the `TestAgentSpecificBehavior` example with `ForEachAgent`, `t.Skip`, etc.). While the new philosophy says \\\"no new test scenarios,\\\" this pattern is still useful for agents with genuinely unique behaviors. Consider keeping it as an appendix or \\\"escape hatch\\\" section.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Minor Suggestions\\n\\n- **implementer.md Step 14 (unit tests):** The instruction to use \\\"real data from E2E runs as golden fixtures\\\" is good but could benefit from a concrete example of how to extract that data (e.g., \\\"copy JSON payloads from `e2e/artifacts/{timestamp}/captures/` into `testdata/` directory\\\").\\n\\n- **SKILL.md parameter table:** The `AGENT_KEY` description says to check `cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go`, but the researcher is told not to read internal source files. This creates a dependency where the user or implementer must derive the key, but the parameter collection happens upfront. Consider noting that `AGENT_KEY` can be deferred to the implement phase.\\n\\n- **Consistency:** The researcher's one-pager template uses `$AGENT_SLUG` in path examples (e.g., `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/settings.json`) but the actual agent package directory uses `$AGENT_PACKAGE`. This is fine since those are different things (config path vs Go package), but a brief note clarifying this would prevent confusion.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Verdict\\n\\nThis is a solid documentation rewrite that reflects real-world learnings from doing agent integrations. The E2E-first approach is pragmatically better for this type of work. The main actionable items are:\\n\\n1. **Fix the typo** (\\\"develpoment\\\" → \\\"development\\\")\\n2. **Soften the researcher restriction** on reading source files\\n3. **Clarify `mise run test` vs compile-only** in Step 3\\n\\nNone of these are blockers — the PR is in good shape overall.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4512,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":85237,\"output_tokens\":1704,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4512,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYd9g5fHDz4T4D4Ps2qQS\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"1c4be101-1bb6-463d-b338-c9efc8b913b6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-01T22:30:03.807Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"1c4be101-1bb6-463d-b338-c9efc8b913b6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"ee198057-0f22-496f-9674-0af8f6e0aa80\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/improve-agent-integration-skill\",\"slug\":\"snoopy-napping-lollipop\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"f87254fb-6469-4e4e-80a7-ad8b17a3743b\",\"toolUseID\":\"f87254fb-6469-4e4e-80a7-ad8b17a3743b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-01T22:30:03.858Z\",\"uuid\":\"f02fa342-bc3e-449e-aa94-b26c1edfc313\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"f02fa342-bc3e-449e-aa94-b26c1edfc313\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"ee198057-0f22-496f-9674-0af8f6e0aa80\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/improve-agent-integration-skill