md was changed from having a \\\"Phase 1: Architecture Inspection\\\" that read many internal files (agent.go, event.go, hook_registry.go, lifecycle.go, agent-guide.md, agent-integration-checklist.md, plus reference implementations) to a simplified \\\"Phase 1: Understand Entire's Expectations\\\" that only reads `agent-guide.md`.\\n\\n\\nThe separation was intentional — the researcher should focus on the external agent interface and documentation rather than diving into Entire's internal implementation, which is the implementer's job. The idea is that `agent-guide.md` provides the stable contract of what Entire expects, while the source files are just implementation details that could change. The researcher only needs the vocabulary and concepts to map the external agent's hooks, not the internal mechanics.\\n\\nBut that breaks down in practice because the documentation can lag behind the actual code, and `agent.go` and `event.go` really are the contract — they're not hidden internals like the strategy or hook registry. So the honest answer is that the reasoning doesn't quite hold up.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":155,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":126355,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":155},\"output_tokens\":12,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYdHA2GUimXwPVnRpu7e6\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"233a87f1-721d-47a1-8aed-29a54c576730\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T00:07:41.751Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"233a87f1-721d-47a1-8aed-29a54c576730\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"ee198057-0f22-496f-9674-0af8f6e0aa80\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/agent-architecture-test\",\"slug\":\"snoopy-napping-lollipop\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_011QAjNEzU3AG3